x4freetext: calculation of the (g,p) reaction cross section from
Proton energy spectra of the (e,p)  reaction  in  the
giant  dipole  resonance  region  of Fe-54 have been
measured at 90-deg  in  steps  of  0.2  MeV  of  the
incident  electron  energy.  The  differential cross
sections of the (g,p0 + p1) and (g,p) reactions were
deduced  from  the  proton  spectra using E1 virtual
photon spectra.  The cross sections are discussed in
terms  of  isospin  splitting  in  the  giant dipole
resonance.  The proton abgular distributions of  the
(e,p0  +  p1)  reaction have been measured also with
electron energies ranging from 16 to 26 MeV in steps
Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
